<br>
possibly due to that everyone seems to agree that there are more important things a government could be doing ..? /shrug<br>
<br>
anyways to continue to where this conversation looks like it be heading..the bible, In my Opinion, (better get that out of the way) the bible and the commandments in all their glory, are merely just a bunch of Decent morals one should live by..'though shall not kill or steal' 'help your brother who is less fortunate' and a story of a man with healing abilities who was to be a 'real nice guy'.<br>
<br>
Im no theologian, but I know (well, knew, for I moved) some friends with PHd's..and I was shocked (a few years ago) that they believed Jesus was actually loaded. Rich. Wealthy. I cant remember the whole words but it was something along the lines of 'frankinscense (sp?) and mihr..were very expensive things, to be called a king would mean riches, and a few other tid bits. (wish I could remember) but this guy was telling me parts of the bible were actually false with this precept and the arguement presented did make some sense. /shrug (if there are any theologians out there, did I remember wrong?)<br>
<br>
My views, and this may seem WAY OFF THE WALL to most of you's ...so dont laugh to hard.<br>
<br>
Much as the scientific community today looks for new technologies, it seems to be a driving desire for man to acheive even more. Be it for medical, commercial, military, exploration, and or money,  the drive is there. <br>
<br>
Now, with that in mind, we currently are involved with space exploration..granted we have a long way to go, but imagine if we started, hmm 4000 years ago , (random number I just chose), we would be farther along today. Im sure we will attempt planet travel and even may try to colonize a planet.<br>
<br>
Now whos to say thats not how 'adam and eve' came about? or even Jesus? Even todays medicine would make someone of that era look like a 'god' in many of eyes. Imagine the medical technology if one also had space exploration technology. And I would think for one, no matter what planet your from, your still gonna wanna 'keep the peace' (to keep from chaos) with teaching your children..what better way than maybe 'your' prophets and belief's in the form of written text. /shrug<br>
<br>
Reason for this train of thought? Well, simple really. All the science books I have ever read, in early times, ALWAYS suggested that man is in the CENTER of everything. remember the flat world? the center of the solar system? the universe? etc etc. Well, in a sense this is the same 'man' who wrote the bible (the original workings? its hard to say. when did  'ink+paper=book'  really start to be?)to say that the almighty-creator of the universe created THIS man on THIS planet is again being, umm, self-centered ? self indulgent? (help me out here at a loss of word) <br>
<br>
anyways, there ya have it. a new version of agnostic.<br>
<br>
Call me a 'few beers short of a six pack' if you will..<br>
 (come to think of it, I mighta been drunk or maybe the bong was a few feet too to tall) /shrug <br>
<br>
But it might make for a good movie someday.<br>
<br>
<br>
..flavors of anonymity.<br>
